HEADWORD: Trespasser
<hw>Tres"pass*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who commits a
trespass</def>; as: <sd>(a)</sd> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>One who enters
upon another's land, or violates his rights.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A
transgressor of the moral law; an offender; a sinner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

